             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a carpenter, I matched this lead, and I am positive it came from the place by the nail-holes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17850629-94-person955">
                  HENRY
                   WARNER
               <interp inst="t17850629-94-person955" type="surname" value="WARNER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850629-94-person955" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850629-94-person955" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>The 10th of May about a quarter past eleven, this man passed me in the street, I am a patrol, and looking after him I saw he had something heavy, I pursued him, and he mended his pace, as I was coming up to lay hold of him he threw the lead down, I sprung my rattle, and he was taken.</p>
               <p>Was he ever out of your sight? - No, I am sure he was the man I first saw with the lead upon his shoulders.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I was going from New Prison, Clerkenwell, with a letter, into Cavendish-street, and one of the watchmen stopped me; I saw a man on the highway.</p>
               <p>The prisoner called one witness who gave him a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17850629-94-verdict456" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17850629-94-verdict456" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17850629-94-punish457" type="punishmentDescription">
